Diagnosed two root-cause bugs:
1. `registries.conf.tpl`: `prefix = ""` (empty string) acts as a catch-all in containers/image format, intercepting all image pulls regardless of source registry. Bootstrap couldn't pull images from correct mirrors → MCS never started → hang at 42%.
2. `os-images-sync.yaml.tpl`: hardcoded `mirror.openshift.com` URLs unreachable in disconnected environments → OS images never registered in AgentServiceConfig.

Fixed:
- `registries.conf.tpl`: only emit `prefix = ...` when non-empty
- `os-images-sync.yaml.tpl`: support `cluster.osImages.{isoUrl,rootFSUrl}` for custom URLs; skip job in disconnected mode without custom URLs
- `acm-ztp.yaml.tpl`: gate os-images-sync on connected or custom URLs
- `schema/clusterfile.schema.json`: add `cluster.osImages` optional fields
