### Prompt 27

> scaling hangs / shows 0 pods and none are starting / [SCC error: fsGroup 1001 not allowed]

Root cause: `fsGroup: 1001` is outside the namespace's allowed supplemental groups range (OpenShift assigns ranges like 1000660000/10000). SCC admission rejects the pod. Fix: remove `fsGroup: 1001` from pod securityContext — OpenShift's restricted-v2 SCC auto-assigns an fsGroup from the namespace range and chowns the PVC mount correctly. Also added `strategy: type: Recreate` to prevent RollingUpdate hang on RWO PVC.

