### Prompt 64

> [ WARNING: operators undefined, substituted 'CHANGEME' ... error parsing STDIN: invalid Yaml document separator: null ] ... cert not found (user showing script still failing + diff of operators config they added to fix it)

Root cause analysis: `LoggingUndefined.__getattr__` adds to `_missing` via `setdefault` on attribute access itself — before `| default({})` can intercept. My v3.19.1 fix used `.operators | default({})` which still triggers the warning via attribute access. The `.get('cert-manager', {})` call then landed on a LoggingUndefined (from `.get` via `__getattr__`), triggering `__getitem__` which calls `_log()` → "operators undefined".

Two bugs fixed:
1. Template: replaced Jinja2 attribute access `.operators` / `.letsencrypt` with Python dict.get() — never creates LoggingUndefined. Verified: completely silent output when operators absent.
2. Script (`steps/common-create-clusterfile-cert-manager-config.sh`): added early exit when provider empty — prevents oc apply on empty output + wrong cert name fallback `letsencrypt-cert`. Script not in git repo, changed in place.

Committed as `fix-cert-manager-logging-undefined` in clusterfile repo.

