### Prompt 69
> HP ilo keeps inserting and ejecting media when booting from ACM.

Root cause: hp vendor was mapped to `redfish-virtualmedia+https` (generic Redfish driver) which causes iLO to loop on insert/eject. Fix: both `hp` and `hpe` now map to `ilo5-virtualmedia://host/redfish/v1/Systems/1` — the native iLO5 driver that handles virtual media lifecycle correctly. Also fixed `hpe` falling through to bare address (was missing from bmc-url.yaml.tpl). Updated schema description to explain the driver selection. Tagged fix-hp-ilo-media-loop.

